│ THOUGHT: The crash happens when creating a shuffle with invalid operands in R.gather: when Root is set, it does Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Root, Vec, Mask). This requires │
│ Root and Vec to be compatible vectors and the mask to match their widths. Vec may still be poison or incorrectly sized, and Root might have a different vector factor,      │
│ leading to isValidOperands failing. I will add a defensive check before emitting the shuffle: if Vec is poison or its vector length differs from Root’s, resize Vec to      │
│ Root’s length using a shuffle with a resize mask or skip combining and just use OriginalRoot. This mirrors the resizing logic already used in                               │
│ ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize and should prevent invalid operands.                                                                                                    │
